In today's update to the Shayna Twitchell disappearance saga, Shayna's ex-boyfriend and father to two of her children Don Carrithers took questions outside the Doral County Sherff's Department after Sheriff William White issued a statement designated the former nightclub employee as a "person of interest" in the case. -- Carrithers answers were such, 
"I'd like some legal representation. But, these police officers have not allowed me to have any. 

I don't know what this is all about. 

I work in that building. Naturally, if I work in that building.

No, they've taken me in because of the fact I live in this area.

I'm st a patsy!"

When Duval County Sheriffs arrived at Don Carrither's trailer, according to Sheriff White's statement, they found him in the back yard burning "dozens and dozens of what appeared to be Russian novels."
